React Experience (What & Why)

I mainly work with functional components and hooks, following modern React standards.

I focus on:

Building reusable UI components

Keeping components clean, readable, and testable

I follow component-driven development, so UI logic, API logic, and state are well separated.

It improves maintainability.

New developers can understand and extend features easily.

Reduces bugs during enhancements.

TypeScript Usage

I use TypeScript across the project to:

Define clear data contracts between UI and backend

Avoid runtime errors

Improve developer confidence while refactoring

TypeScript helps especially in large applications where multiple developers work on the same codebase.

Real impact

Fewer production issues.

Faster code reviews.

Better collaboration across teams.

State Management & Performance

Based on project size, I choose:

Context API for small to medium apps

Redux Toolkit for complex global state

I actively work on performance optimization, such as:

Reducing unnecessary re-renders

Optimizing component structure

Splitting large components into smaller ones

API Integration

I have experience integrating REST and GraphQL APIs.

I ensure:

